醫學工程研究所


 



學經歷：


 
學歷： 
(1)PhD, Institute of Electrical Engineering, National Taiwan University
(2)Master, Institute of Electrical Engineering, National Taiwan University

經歷： 
(1)Assistant Professor, Institute of Biomedical Engineering, National Taiwan University of Science and Technology, 2010/08 till now
(2) Assistant Professor, Department of Electrical Engineering, Yuan Ze University, 2003/08-2010/07
(3)Postdoc, Institute of Physics, Academia Sinica, 2001/08-2003/07




專業技術



 
1. 醫學工程
2. 生醫光電
3. 血液循環力學
4. 微循環血流訊號分析


 
 


專利介紹



 







 
穴位體表光學式血流狀態評估應用於糖尿病早期偵測之系統
 






 
建立一體表非侵入光學檢測裝置，量取體表穴位血管床之血流特性參數。由於穴道會比非穴道部位具有更豐富的血......









 










 
一改善腕部動脈血壓波形擷取便利性，應用於慢性疾病早期偵測與病程監控之生醫電子儀器量測裝置與配合機構
 






 
建立一量測裝置與配合機構，與壓力感應器結合使用，改善腕部動脈血壓波形擷取之便利性，以應用於慢性疾病早......









 





 
 
 


研究計畫



 
教授課程
1.微積分[Calculus(Ⅰ)]
2.循環生理訊號學
3.生醫資訊處理[Biomedical Signal Process]
榮譽獎項
指導大學專題生得獎
(1) 元智大學工學院大學部 94年度論文比賽特優(程健銘、王敬懿、許家良、何國廷)：結合溫度壓力控制紅外光血壓波形量測系統之架設與初步測試
(2) 元智大學工學院大學部 95年度論文比賽優等(詹千蓁、王韻茹)：微循環生理狀態評估系統之加熱效應研究
期刊論文
1. Hsin Hsiu, Chia-Liang Hsu, Ming-Yie Jan. Relations between beat-to-beat
microcirculatory blood flow and variations therein. Photomed Laser Surg, accepted (SCI,
IF=1.785, 53/148, Surgery).
2. Hsin Hsiu, Wei-Chen Hsu, Chia-Liang Hsu, Shih-Ming Huang. Assessing the effects of
acupuncture by comparing needling the Hegu acupoint and needling nearby
nonacupoints by spectral analysis of microcirculatory laser Doppler signals. Accepted,
Evid Based Complement Alternat Med. (SCI, IF=1.954, 5/14, Integrative and
Complementary Medicine).
3. Hsin Hsiu, Wei-Chen Hsu, Bo-Hung Chen, Chia-Liang Hsu. Different microcirculatory
effects between acupuncture point and non-acupoint by applying local skin-surface
contacting pressure stimulation – possible relevance with acupressure. Physiol. Meas. 31
(2010) 829-841 (SCI, IF=1.691, 27/51, Biomedical Engineering)
4. Hsin Hsiu, Wei-Chen Hsu, Chia-Liang Hsu, Shih-Ming Huang, Yuh-Ying Lin Wang.
Microcirculatory changes by laser Doppler after infra-red heating over acupuncture
points – relevance to moxibustion. Photomed Laser Surg 27(6): 855-61, 2009. (SCI,
IF=1.785, 53/148, Surgery)
